### Proposal

Currently the [Abbreviation styles](https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.2/content/typography/#abbreviations) show the dotted underline on all browsers, even mobile devices where it isn't possible to hover over them to show the title.

I'd like to propose that the styles for `abbr` and `.initialism` be limited to only browsers/devices which support the [hover:hover media query](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@media/hover) (namely iOS/iPadOS) by updating reboot.scss. I think it'd look something like this:

```css
@media (hover: none) {
  abbr[title] {
    -webkit-text-decoration: none;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
}

@media (hover: hover) {
  abbr[title] {
    text-decoration: underline dotted;
    cursor: help;
    text-decoration-skip-ink: none;
  }
}
```

I've tested this on desktop Chrome 102, Edge 102 and it works exactly as expected there  - the text is not underlined on iPadOS 15, iOS 15 and Android 7 (Chrome 102) where it isn't possible to see the title - even with a pointing device (mouse) connected.

